message.content:
Rule Learning, Case Based. 

Rule Learning is present in the text as the authors discuss the formal integrated model of knowledge for design, which includes knowledge for planning steps in design and problem-solving knowledge that supports design. This model is based on the task-structure, which guides both acquisition and application of knowledge. 

Case Based is also present in the text as the authors discuss the different types of knowledge that enter the knowledge base of a design support system, including problem-solving knowledge. The authors also give an account of possibilities for problem solving depending on the knowledge that is at the disposal of the system, which is a key aspect of case-based reasoning.
